videos.headline: Verdell takes off for 89-yard Oregon TD
videos.description: CJ Verdell finds the open gap and takes off untouched as he runs 89 yards for the Oregon touchdown.

videos.headline: WSU QB slams his head in frustration
videos.description: After turning the ball over, Washington State quarterback Anthony Gordon hits his head against what appears to be a trunk lid on the sidelines.

videos.headline: WSU pass turns into pick-six for Ducks
videos.description: Oregon defender Jevon Holland picks off Anthony Gordon and returns the interception 19 yards for a touchdown late in the second quarter.

videos.headline: WSU ties it up before halftime
videos.description: Washington State quarterback Anthony Gordon finds WR Renard Bell who takes it in 15 yards to tie the game at 17 against No. 11 Oregon.

videos.headline: Verdell powers in for 2-yard TD
videos.description: Oregon's CJ Verdell gives it all he's got to power into the end zone as the Ducks take the lead over Washington State in the third quarter.

videos.headline: Gordon finds Arconado in end zone to take lead
videos.description: Washington State's Anthony Gordon finds a wide-open Brandon Arconado in the end zone as the Cougars take a 1-point lead over Oregon late in the fourth.

videos.headline: Ducks hit game-winning FG as time expires
videos.description: Oregon kicker Camden Lewis drills a 26-yard field goal as time expires to give the Ducks a big win over Washington State 37-35.
